spans.text: The purple stream that through my vessels glides , Dull and unconscious

I , no more than they : This frame compacted with transcendent skill , Of moving joints obedient to my will , Nursed from the fruitful glebae , like yonder tree , Waxes and wastes ; I call it mine , not me
superior lineage by my SIRE , Who warmed the unthinking clod with heavenly fire : Essence divine , with lifeless clay allayed , By double nature , double instinct swayed
I range from pole to pole
Through the same trackless paths of boundless void
off from heavenly truth this reasoning me
from heavenly truth this reasoning me
By adverse gusts of jarring instincts tossed
in haste , One moment gives the pleasure and distaste
the first replies , Thou art a god
I know too little or too much
this faint glimmering of thyself away
The balm , the light , the guide of souls perplexed
no less thy pedigree , What thou once wert
no less thy pedigree , What thou once wert
has power to rove : Who acts by force impelled
to grow a god by doing ill
not to regain thy native sky , Born on the wings of vain philosophy
Mysterious passage ! hid from human eyes
humble thoughts thy wary footsteps guide
meekness what you lost by pride
